HEADWORD: Terek
<hw>Ter"ek</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Because found on the
<etsep>Terek</etsep> River in the Caucasus.]</ety> <def>A sandpiper
(<spn>Terekia cinerea</spn>) of the Old World, breeding in the far north
of eastern Europe and Asia and migrating to South Africa and Australia.
It frequents rivers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

